</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F02FF95FF26F95DFCFDF8F8" blockId="55.[151,1437,1251,1961]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
Habitat. Infralittoral and circalittoral species, known from 
<quantity id="2E379B383F02FF95FCB7F95DFC59F917" box="[854,953,1755,1782]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.25" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" unit="m" value="62.5" valueMax="120.0" valueMin="5.0">5–120 m</quantity>
depth on soft bottoms with mud, sand, silt, shell or small-stone deposits (Miller 1986; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F02FF95FD98F886FCF0F8F8" author="Patzner, R. A." box="[633,784,1791,1818]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refId="ref62855" refString="Patzner, R. A. (2021) Gobiidae. Available from: http: // www. patzner. sbg. ac. at / Gobiidae / GobiidaeSpecies. htm (accessed 1 October 2021)" type="url" year="2021">Patzner 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F02FF95FF26F8A5FD4EF848" blockId="55.[151,1437,1251,1961]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
Geographic distribution. Eastern Atlantic from 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F02FF95FD0DF8A5FC63F8DC" box="[748,899,1827,1853]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Great Britain</collectingCountry>
(Miller 1974) to Madeira and Canary Islands (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F02FF95FF7EF8C1FEC9F880" author="Miller, P. J." box="[159,297,1863,1889]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="363 - 412" refId="ref61539" refString="Miller, P. J. (1984) The gobiid fishes of temperate Macaronesia (eastern Atlantic). Journal of Zoology, London, 204, 363 - 412. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1984. tb 02379. x" type="journal article" year="1984">Miller 1984</bibRefCitation>
) and in the western Mediterranean: Alboran and Balearic Islands (
